  "text": "The operators (2.13) differ from the ones considered by Distler [CITATION_1] , which are not SL(2) invariant. In [CITATION_2] a further operation of \"picture changing\" was necessary in order to obtain non-zero correlators. In that language, the operators (2.13) are already in the correct picture and in principle their correlators can be evaluated without any extra screening insertions. The only selection rule comes from anomalous conservation of Liouville momentum, and it is precisely (1.5).",
